rComments: Not a very good prof, lectures were extremely boring, hard to follow, and unorganized.

This prof does not understand primarily the material that she is teaching. She reads off the power point and does not have answers for basic questions regarding the subject. She falls behind and therefore crams everything  the weekend before the exam. Would not recommend any classes with her. Change ASAP. VERY hard marker on uncovered material.

Awful prof, doesn't understand the material she is trying to teach. She has a lot of difficulty explaining concepts as she essentially reads directly from her notes. I would suggest heavy use of the textbook if you have to have her.

She has no idea how to teach. Others have said it was because she is new but she still has not improved. After 4 weeks, we were already 3 topics behind the other section. Avoid at all costs, and if you can't don't bother going to class and just read the textbook.

Although this prof cant always explain her thoughts well, she is very organized, making it easy to study for this class. She does not rush through lectures like many of the other anatomy profs, which allows time to relax and not panic about getting behind.

This professor has difficulty in class explaining content and does not respond to students. She is also not very "nice" when dealing with students. Her slides are confusing. She is a new professor so perhaps she will get better.

Hated this class, and this prof is extremely frustrating. Does not answer questions on VC (waits until students answer or says the TAs can answer), feedback on midterms are useless, says you don't need to study something for the exam but it'll be on there, has no confidence when lecturing, and there is no textbook to help out. Avoid her.

She reads off the slides but I'd rather that than her putting blanks in her slides like other profs. She says "um" a lot which is annoying, isn't always concise when answering your question, and doesn't look at he class enough in case someone has their hand raised. But she's a new and young prof so her best days are ahead of her.
